EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Has quest for Moonrise towers

Text.Value: Forward, then. No curse will keep me from purification.
Whatever. I'm not afraid of the dark.
I do have a Moonlantern, as it happens. Right here in my pouch.
One of Nere's magic lamps. You won't last without one.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Does not have quest for Moonrise towers

Text.Value: Must be the shadow curse. I really don't think we should go wandering in without protection.
My thoughts exactly.
He speaks of the shadow curse. Forget Nere and the Moonlantern - if we're this close to the surface, we must chance the journey.
Excellent. The less time I have to spend with these underdwarves, the better.
Excellent. The less time I have to spend with these underdwarves, the better. Present company excluded, of course.
The shadow curse. We'll need that Moonlantern from Nere to survive the journey to Moonrise Towers.
So we're going up there without the lantern? I hope you know what you're doing.
Sounds like the shadow curse. We must be getting close. Forget Nere and the Moonlantern -  let's just press on.
Erm. Shouldn't we go grab that Moonlantern before wandering into what sounds an awful lot like an abyss?
Shit - good thing, too. You won't get far without one.
Let's just hope you're right. Otherwise we're just aiding the enemy.
Chk - more time wasted. If only you feared the ghaik parasite half as much as you fear the dark.
We were warned about the curse. Can't say I fancy our chances without a Moonlantern.
A Moonlantern? What's that?
Gotta be done. Let's go.
'Death-dark'? What are you talking about?
That Moonlantern is key to our survival. And that means freeing Nere.
If the cure's in Moonrise, we should go, Nere and his lantern be damned. After all, 'shadows' will be the least of our worries if we start to turn.
Go on up, if you fancy. Me? I'd sooner take a swim in the Darklake.
Thanks for sharing. I'll keep it in mind.
'Death-dark' doesn't sound very inviting. Can't say I fancy our chances without freeing Nere and getting that Moonlantern.
Let's just go, Nere and the Moonlantern be damned. After everything we've been through, I think we can handle a few shadows.
A stab in the dark it is...
Afraid of the dark, are we? Very well - let us save Nere, if we must.
Leave.
I don't have a Moonlantern. So what?
The surface is within reach. Forget Nere, forget the Moonlantern - I hardly fear a few shadows.
It's your funeral. And mine. I'm not ready!
There we have it. Let 'Operation Free Nere' commence.
We should move on, 'death-dark' or not.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Does not have Halsin quest for Moonrise towers

Text.Value: Good. After all we've been through, this is hardly the time to falter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Approving of the player's decision to press onwards through danger to their goal

Text.Value: That Moonlantern is key to our survival. And that means freeing Nere.
Shadows - thick as a duerro's skull. Sucks the breath right out of your lungs.
Moonrise Towers holds the answers we seek. Curse or not, we can't turn back now.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Does not have Halsin quest for Moonrise towers

Text.Value: You're going up there? You've either got iron guts - or one of those Moonlanterns.
I'm not so keen on taking a shadow-nap, myself. We need to free Nere and get that Moonlantern.
No surprises that there's danger ahead, but at least we're getting closer. Leave Nere to rot - we should press on.
The death-dark's clogged the top-land, clear to Moonrise Towers. Only a Moonlantern dispels it.
Leave.
Well you should be. That stuff will end you in two flaps of a batwing.
So you won't be getting far - not without one of Nere's magic lamps.

Synopsis: Player clicks on elevator leading to the shadow-cursed lands. Nearby gnome  butts in to let you know you don't look like you're in any shape to go up there. The land is cursed, and you need a moonlantern. Plays only once.
